Engineer - Chemical

Savannah River Remediation

- Aiken, SC 29808

Savannah River Remediation is seeking Chemical Engineers to be based in our Aiken, SC location on the Savannah River Site.
The Chemical Engineer implements solutions to mechanical, chemical, electrical and/or nuclear solutions to meet standards set by the Department of Energy (DOE) for the Savannah River Remediation (SRR) project.
Assume technical responsibility for one or more phases of a program and/or ownership for unit operations within processing facilities.
Collaborate with colleagues to provide innovative improvements to the existing processes.
Specific job responsibilities many involve the following assignments: project engineering support, facility engineering support, process flow sheet analysis and development, procurement requirements and specifications development, technical calculations and reviews, design reviews, safety analysis development, and commercial grade dedication.
Performs comprehensive engineering solutions to broadly defined and moderately complex activities.
Performs studies, development, testing and analysis of designs, processes and/or procedures as part of a multi-disciplinary team.
Explores approaches and recommends improvements under moderate guidance from Manager and/or higher level engineers.
Collaborate with facility/department colleagues.
Apply training of SRR and specific department systems, methodologies and requirements for accomplishing tasks. Including but not limited to appropriate use of the proper tools and protective equipment required to complete tasks.
May provide guidance and/or informal mentoring to new engineers.
May present/explain technical information to members of team, department or facility

